araucaria schmidii (schmid araucaria) is a species of conifer in the araucariaceae family. it is a medium to large tree growing up to 30 meters tall. it is found only in a small area on new caledonia, with only one contiguous population in an area covering less than one square kilometer on the summit and highest slopes of mont pani√© in the north-east of the main island, grande terre, though a few scattered individuals may still be found on surrounding peaks. it is threatened by habitat loss. while the single remaining population is in a protected national park in a remote area, this area is still regularly visited by tourists, and iucn has expressed concern that the entire population is at risk of being wiped out by a chance event such as the introduction of a fungal disease (e.g. phytophthora).